A recent report highlights the critical role of agricultural water in the Colorado basin amid concerns of water scarcity due to climate change.
Global warming is projected to exacerbate droughts and diminish river flows, impacting urban and agricultural water needs.
The looming water shortages may lead to reallocation from farms to urban areas, sparking conflicts and migration.
Efforts are underway to address water scarcity, including potential water shortages by 2010.
Conservation measures and agreements among states aim to manage water resources sustainably amidst growing demands and environmental concerns.
